features: CRISPY WITHOUT THE CALORIES: Don't sacrifice great taste for healthy cooking. Serve all the delicious fried foods your family loves using 98% less oil. Air fry vegetables, pizza, frozen foods, and even leftovers to a perfect crisp in minutes
PERFECT TIMING: Get rid of the guesswork with four one-touch preset cooking functions for popular dishes like French fries, chicken, fish, and meat and start frying in seconds.
EVENLY CRISP: A built-in LED Shake reminder with an alarm lets you know when it's time to give your food a shake to ensure evenly crisped food every time.
VERSATILE TEMPS: With a cooking temperature range of 200-400°F, you can create the perfect dish no matter what's on the menu. Lower temps cook food with less crunch, higher temps for more.
EASY TO CLEAN: The removable air fryer basket and the cooking tray is dishwasher-safe, and the exterior easily wipes down with a cloth.
AUTOMATIC SHUTOFF: Heating pauses when the basket is opened and restarts where it left off when replaced. Once the timer goes off and cooking is complete, the unit will automatically shut off.
QUICK COOKING: This 5-quart large air fryer is perfect for feeding the whole family or about 3-4 people and is designed to get dinner on the table in minutes
COUNTERTOP CHIC: The streamlined design of this 5-quart air fryer has an impressive capacity without taking up too much valuable space on your kitchen countertop.
RESOURCES: cETL approved with advanced safety technology for long lasting durability, & 1-year assurance provided by Chefman. 120 Volts/1500 Watts – RJ38-SQSS-5T
body.description: Air frying for the family is so convenient with the Chefman TurboFry® Touch 5-Quart Air Fryer. With effortless one-touch digital controls and four built-in presets, you can cook your favorite foods to the perfect fried finish every time. An adjustable temperature range of 200-400°F gives you complete control, while an automatic shake reminder ensures even cooking. The dishwasher-safe nonstick 5qt basket capacity allows you to feed the whole family, and the stainless-steel exterior wipes down simply with a damp cloth. Purchase includes a 1-year assurance from Chefman. For information on how to use your product, scroll down for a PDF User Guide. 120 Volts/1500 Watts –RJ38-SQSS-5T • One-touch digital display • Four preset cooking functions • Large 5-quart capacity • LED shake reminder for even cooking • Temperature range from 200°F to 400°F • Sleek, space-saving design • Easy-to-clean nonstick basket • Dishwasher-safe parts

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars VERY Nice Air Fryer!
reviews.reviewText: I wanted to wait awhile before I gave my review of the Chefman Air Fryer. I have it now one month and am enjoying it quite a bit. Lots of use! My adult daughter is staying temporarily and loving it as well. We are the main users. I love that it's roomy and QUIET! LOL The basket interior is quite roomy for at least a FIVE POUND Whole Chicken! Spacious enough for a tasty 5-6 lb Beef or Pork Roast. You can place about 10-12 whole wings in there at a time. Grilled Cheese, etc, etc. To go with this Fryer, I would suggest and recommend the "Elctbras 4 Pack Air Fryer Silicone Liners Reusable Round Insert, Food Grade Silicone Liners for AirFryers up to 8 quart." - they also can be used in microwave. I HIGHLY RECOMMEND these as they come in very handy to place in your Air Fryer and help keep it a bit cleaner, longer. For instance, with these Silicone liners, they are placed right in your fryer. You can place fries, whole potatoes, cut bagels/English muffins, and all sorts of foods. They are round, absolutely reusable to and hand and machine washable). They dry very fast then ready to use again. THEY CONE IN A SET OF FOUR for around $20.00, maybe a bit less depending when purchased. Of course you can use your Air Fryer as well without the liners whenever you desire; they are just a little helpful addition. If you're toasting/Air frying your bagel, muffin, etc. in the fryer, I place it in the Silicone liner. Only a few crumbs remain and get shaken clean till next time. If Air frying a meal of sorts, you can place directly in your Non-stick air fryer as well. Cook as desired. The basket is very easy to clean. You can hand wash in very warm to hot water with a liquid detergent like Dawn. If need be, lightly brush with a dish brush, then rinse and drip dry. A quick wipe and place back in the unit. Or place in your dishwasher. Rest of Air Fryer gets a wipe with soft cloth. Overall,I definitely recommend this very attractive and quite impressive Air Fryer!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars First Air Fryer
reviews.reviewText: WOW. Why did I wait so long before getting an air fryer? I am not a person that likes alot of appliances setting around, especially if I don't use them. So I did read alot on the varieties of fryers before chosing. Just received this Chefman 8 qt air fryer. Cranked it up and put in some chicken wings. They were so good. Perfect. Clean up was super easy. Let it completely cool. Stuck the grate in soapy water. Used a paper towel to wipe out what grease there was and put in soapy water - poof. Easy. I am excited about this fryer and really looking forward to eating healthier with less hassel. Everything about this unit is easy - easy to use, easy to clean and nice and a nice big basket. Very happy - thank you.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I previously owned an air fryer. My first. It was just ok until it was recalled. I am glad that we got the run around for the replacement because we gave up on them and purchased this one. I am very happy with this product. It does everything it claims to do. It is very easy to run, and I have had no trouble understanding the directions for it's use. After you cool the pans down (for Teflon linings a must), it cleans like a dream. I purchased the 8 qt. size and am so happy for the extra space to cook with. My hubby loves it for heating up left over pizza. It comes out nice and crispy on the bottom just like fresh baked.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I’ve been hearing all about the buzz on how wonderful air fryers are—healthy, convenient and cooks almost anything you’d place in an oven.I did a lot of research and wanted to make sure my first air fryer didn’t contain Teflon or those forever chemicals. Articles I read mentioned that Chefman’s do not. I didn’t need something too big yet I didn’t want a tiny one.This air fryer at 5 quarts is perfect. Anything breaded turns out crispy and delicious. Zucchini fries (or even potato) are addictive. Glazed wings—-delicious.Easy to clean and the basket for cooking is large.So why not 5 stars? My device’s tray came damaged. The hinge to pick it up was missing. I spoke to Chefman support several times and I’m still on the waitlist for a part replacement. I bought it back in July and they would have gladly replaced it but it meant returning this product to UPS and although not heavy, it’s also not light. I can still use the device by lifting the tray with a fork or knife but it’s just the principle and somewhat clumsy.I am still hoping to receive the replacement for the tray—otherwise it just works so wonderfully. I love food cooked in this air fryer.It’s as though the food is transported to a restaurant and comes back so delicious. It’s like magic and cooking time is quick.User friendly too.Recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quiet and Sleek
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for my limited vision father. His old air fryer finally quit working efficiently and he was due for a new one. I bought this one because of the great reviews and I'm just going to add to it. This thing is so quiet! We were shocked. We had to keep checking that it was running Because of how quiet it is. Amazing! Also, with his limited vision, he needs very bright displays and this display is very bright and works great for him. I thought I'd mention that in case anyone else has limited vision. My father loves the basket size and the sleek design. I am looking to buy myself one now. Love it.
